### AuraEvents — event creation flow (Postgres + Umbraco) end-to-end tests
### Requires the VS Code "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client).
### Run requests top-to-bottom with "Send Request" — each captures values the next one needs.
###
### Prerequisites:
### 1. `docker compose up --build` running (Identity.Api :5001, Events.Api :5002, Umbraco :5003).
### 2. An Organizer/Admin user to log in as. There's no self-service role promotion (documented
###    limitation) — register normally via the frontend/Identity.Api, then grant the role directly:
###      UPDATE user_roles ... -- or INSERT INTO user_roles (user_id, role_id)
###      SELECT u.user_id, r.role_id FROM users u, roles r
###      WHERE u.email = 'organizer@auraevents.local' AND r.name = 'Organizer';
### 3. For the "via BFF" section: `cd frontend/web-app && npm run dev` (port 3000), and enable
###    the REST Client cookie jar so the login sets a real session:
###      "rest-client.enableCookieJar": true   (VS Code settings.json)

@identityApiUrl = http://localhost:5001
@eventsApiUrl = http://localhost:5002
@frontendUrl = http://localhost:3000
@organizerEmail = organizer@auraevents.local
@organizerPassword = ChangeMe123!


### =========================================================================
### SECTION 1 — direct-to-backend happy path (Events.Api owns the orchestration,
### this is what both the BFF and, in tests, we call directly)
### =========================================================================

### 1.1 Log in as Organizer/Admin via Identity.Api to get a bearer token
# @name login
POST {{identityApiUrl}}/api/identity/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{organizerEmail}}",
  "password": "{{organizerPassword}}"
}

###
@accessToken = {{login.response.body.accessToken}}


### 1.2 Create an event WITH AI content — this is what NewEventForm.tsx submits after the
### "generate content with AI" step. Exercises: Postgres insert -> Umbraco create -> Umbraco
### publish -> Postgres link (systemEventId <-> UmbracoContentKey).
# @name createEvent
POST {{eventsApiUrl}}/api/events
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "AuraEvents QA Night {{$guid}}",
  "slug": "auraevents-qa-night-{{$guid}}",
  "startAtUtc": "2026-09-10T17:00:00Z",
  "endAtUtc": "2026-09-10T20:00:00Z",
  "timezone": "Asia/Jerusalem",
  "venueName": "Tel Aviv HQ",
  "isVirtual": false,
  "capacity": 150,
  "status": "Published",
  "umbracoContentKey": null,
  "content": {
    "summary": "ערב QA פתוח לקהילת AuraEvents — הדגמות חיות ומפגש עם הצוות.",
    "description": "הצטרפו אלינו לערב מבחנים פתוח: נעבור על התכונות האחרונות, נריץ הדגמות חיות ונשמח לשמוע פידבק ישיר מהקהילה.",
    "seoTitle": "AuraEvents QA Night — תל אביב",
    "seoDescription": "ערב QA פתוח של AuraEvents בתל אביב — הדגמות, שיחות, ומפגש עם הצוות."
  }
}

###
@eventId = {{createEvent.response.body.eventId}}

### Expect: 201 Created, body.umbracoContentKey is a non-null GUID, body.umbracoSyncError is null.


### 1.3 Confirm the link persisted (re-fetch from Postgres, not from memory)
GET {{eventsApiUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Expect: same umbracoContentKey as 1.2, not null.


### 1.4 Confirm the Umbraco side: the node exists, is published, and is discoverable via the
### same Delivery API the public homepage uses.
GET {{eventsApiUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/availability
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###
GET http://localhost:5003/umbraco/delivery/api/v2/content?filter=contentType:eventPage&filter=systemEventId:{{eventId}}

### Expect: one item, with properties.systemEventId == {{eventId}}.


### =========================================================================
### SECTION 2 — retry endpoint (POST /api/events/{id}/umbraco-content)
### =========================================================================

### 2.1 Create an event WITHOUT content (content: null) — mirrors an organizer who filled in
### logistics but the AI step was skipped/failed client-side. No Umbraco call happens here.
# @name createEventNoContent
POST {{eventsApiUrl}}/api/events
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "AuraEvents Retry Test {{$guid}}",
  "slug": "auraevents-retry-test-{{$guid}}",
  "startAtUtc": "2026-10-01T17:00:00Z",
  "endAtUtc": "2026-10-01T20:00:00Z",
  "timezone": "Asia/Jerusalem",
  "venueName": "Tel Aviv HQ",
  "isVirtual": false,
  "capacity": 100,
  "status": "Draft",
  "umbracoContentKey": null,
  "content": null
}

###
@noContentEventId = {{createEventNoContent.response.body.eventId}}

### Expect: 201 Created, umbracoContentKey: null, umbracoSyncError: null (not requested, not a failure).


### 2.2 Retry — this is the "נסה שוב לפרסם" button's request
# @name retryPublish
POST {{eventsApiUrl}}/api/events/{{noContentEventId}}/umbraco-content
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "summary": "תקציר שנוצר בניסיון החוזר.",
  "description": "תיאור מלא שנוצר בניסיון החוזר, אחרי שהיצירה הראשונית לא כללה תוכן.",
  "seoTitle": "AuraEvents Retry Test",
  "seoDescription": "בדיקת נתיב ה-retry ליצירת תוכן ב-Umbraco."
}

### Expect: 200 OK, umbracoContentKey now populated, umbracoSyncError: null.


### 2.3 Retry again on the same (now-linked) event — must be rejected, not create a second node
POST {{eventsApiUrl}}/api/events/{{noContentEventId}}/umbraco-content
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "summary": "ניסיון כפול — אמור להיכשל.",
  "description": "...",
  "seoTitle": "...",
  "seoDescription": "..."
}

### Expect: 409 Conflict, error.code == "CONTENT_ALREADY_LINKED".


### =========================================================================
### SECTION 3 (optional) — same happy path through the actual Next.js BFF, proving the
### frontend Route Handlers (not just Events.Api directly) work end-to-end. Requires
### `npm run dev` in frontend/web-app and rest-client.enableCookieJar = true.
### =========================================================================

### 3.1 Log in via the BFF (sets httpOnly session cookies on this REST Client "browser")
POST {{frontendUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{organizerEmail}}",
  "password": "{{organizerPassword}}"
}

###

### 3.2 Submit the same payload NewEventForm.tsx would build, through the BFF proxy
# @name createEventViaBff
POST {{frontendUrl}}/api/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "AuraEvents BFF Path Test {{$guid}}",
  "slug": "auraevents-bff-path-test-{{$guid}}",
  "startAtUtc": "2026-09-15T17:00:00Z",
  "endAtUtc": "2026-09-15T20:00:00Z",
  "timezone": "Asia/Jerusalem",
  "venueName": "Tel Aviv HQ",
  "isVirtual": false,
  "capacity": 80,
  "status": "Published",
  "umbracoContentKey": null,
  "content": {
    "summary": "בדיקת הנתיב המלא דרך ה-BFF.",
    "description": "מוודא שה-Route Handler מעביר את הבקשה נכון ומחזיר את אותה תשובה כמו קריאה ישירה ל-Events.Api.",
    "seoTitle": "AuraEvents BFF Path Test",
    "seoDescription": "בדיקת proxy מה-Next.js BFF אל Events.Api."
  }
}

### Expect: identical shape/behavior to 1.2, proxied through Next.js.


### =========================================================================
### SECTION 4 — rollback test: force a Postgres failure *after* Umbraco already published,
### and confirm the orphaned node gets cleaned up. Uses the Development-only
### `simulateDbFailureAfterUmbracoPublish` query flag (EventsController.cs) — inert unless
### Events.Api is running with ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT=Development (the docker-compose default).
### See docs/testing/umbraco-swagger-verification.md for the full log-reading walkthrough.
### =========================================================================

# @name simulateRollback
POST {{eventsApiUrl}}/api/events?simulateDbFailureAfterUmbracoPublish=true
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "AuraEvents Rollback Test {{$guid}}",
  "slug": "auraevents-rollback-test-{{$guid}}",
  "startAtUtc": "2026-09-20T17:00:00Z",
  "endAtUtc": "2026-09-20T20:00:00Z",
  "timezone": "Asia/Jerusalem",
  "venueName": "Tel Aviv HQ",
  "isVirtual": false,
  "capacity": 50,
  "status": "Published",
  "umbracoContentKey": null,
  "content": {
    "summary": "בדיקת rollback — לא אמור להישאר node יתום ב-Umbraco.",
    "description": "אם ה-cleanup עובד נכון, ה-node הזה יימחק מ-Umbraco ברגע שה-SaveChanges המדומה נכשל.",
    "seoTitle": "AuraEvents Rollback Test",
    "seoDescription": "בדיקת ניקוי node יתום ב-Umbraco."
  }
}

###
@rollbackEventId = {{simulateRollback.response.body.eventId}}

### Expect: 201 Created, umbracoContentKey: null, umbracoSyncError populated.
### Then check Docker logs and Umbraco (see docs/testing/umbraco-swagger-verification.md).


### 4.1 Confirm Postgres agrees there's no link (not just that the response said so)
GET {{eventsApiUrl}}/api/events/{{rollbackEventId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Expect: umbracoContentKey: null.


### 4.2 The retry endpoint should still work normally afterwards (no leftover state blocking it)
POST {{eventsApiUrl}}/api/events/{{rollbackEventId}}/umbraco-content
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "summary": "פרסום תקין אחרי ה-rollback.",
  "description": "מוודא שאין מצב תקוע אחרי הכשל המדומה.",
  "seoTitle": "AuraEvents Rollback Test",
  "seoDescription": "פרסום מוצלח אחרי rollback."
}

### Expect: 200 OK, umbracoContentKey now populated (a *new* node — the failed one was deleted,
### not reused).

